[[Some applications of relative homology|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uLn5RsX0648&index=29&list=PL7BFF10190F42006E]]

[ext[Some examples|https://www.math.cornell.edu/~hatcher/AT/AT.pdf#page=127]]:

: $$H_i(D^n, \partial D^n) = \begin{cases}\mathbb{Z}~~\text{for}~i=n\\ 0~~ \text{otherwise}\end{cases}$$

: $$H_n(X,x_0) \cong \tilde{H}_n(X)$$ for all $$n$$ since $$\tilde{H}_n(x_0) = 0$$ for all $$n$$.

Similarly to normal homology, homotopic maps between pairs of spaces induce the same homomorphisms between the correponding relative homologies.

